{"name": "mbstrdecoder", "metadata": {"name": "mbstrdecoder", "version": "1.1.3", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Intended Audience :: Information Technology", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules", "Topic :: Text Processing"], "home_page": "https://github.com/thombashi/mbstrdecoder", "license": "MIT License", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["chardet"], "summary": "mbstrdecoder is a Python library for multi-byte character string decoder", "upload_time": 1686387259}, "documentation": ["```{contents} **mbstrdecoder**\n:backlinks: top\n:local: true\n```\n\n# Summary\n\n[mbstrdecoder](https://github.com/thombashi/mbstrdecoder) is a Python library for multi-byte character string decoder.\n\n```{image} https://badge.fury.io/py/mbstrdecoder.svg\n:alt: PyPI package version\n:target: https://badge.fury.io/py/mbstrdecoder\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/mbstrdecoder.svg\n:target: |-\n:  https://pypi.org/project/mbstrdecoder\n:  :alt: Supported Python versions\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/implementation/mbstrdecoder.svg\n:alt: Supported Python implementations\n:target: https://pypi.org/project/mbstrdecoder\n```\n\n```{image} https://github.com/thombashi/mbstrdecoder/actions/workflows/lint_and_test.yml/badge.svg\n:alt: CI status of Linux/macOS/Windows\n:target: https://github.com/thombashi/mbstrdecoder/actions/workflows/lint_and_test.yml\n```\n\n```{image} https://coveralls.io/repos/github/thombashi/mbstrdecoder/badge.svg?branch=master\n:alt: Test coverage\n:target: https://coveralls.io/github/thombashi/mbstrdecoder?branch=master\n```\n\n```{image} https://github.com/thombashi/mbstrdecoder/actions/workflows/codeql-analysis.yml/badge.svg\n:alt: CodeQL\n:target: https://github.com/thombashi/mbstrdecoder/actions/workflows/codeql-analysis.yml\n```\n\n# Installation\n\n## Install from PyPI\n\n```\npip install mbstrdecoder\n```\n\n## Install from PPA (for Ubuntu)\n\n```\nsudo add-apt-repository ppa:thombashi/ppa\nsudo apt update\nsudo apt install python3-mbstrdecoder\n```\n\n# Usage\n\n```\nSample Code\n\npython\n\nfrom mbstrdecoder import MultiByteStrDecoder\n\nencoded_multibyte_text = \"\u30de\u30eb\u30c1\u30d0\u30a4\u30c8\u6587\u5b57\".encode(\"utf-8\")\ndecoder = MultiByteStrDecoder(encoded_multibyte_text)\n\nprint(\"encoded bytes: {}\".format(encoded_multibyte_text))\nprint(\"unicode: {}\".format(decoder.unicode_str))\nprint(\"codec: {}\".format(decoder.codec))\n\nOutput\n\nencoded bytes: b'\\xe3\\x83\\x9e\\xe3\\x83\\xab\\xe3\\x83\\x81\\xe3\\x83\\x90\\xe3\\x82\\xa4\\xe3\\x83\\x88\\xe6\\x96\\x87\\xe5\\xad\\x97'\nunicode: \u30de\u30eb\u30c1\u30d0\u30a4\u30c8\u6587\u5b57\ncodec: utf_8\n```\n\n# Dependencies\n\n- Python 3.7+\n- [Python package dependencies (automatically installed)](https://github.com/thombashi/mbstrdecoder/network/dependencies)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "mbstrdecoder.__version__", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "mbstrdecoder.__version__.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mbstrdecoder.__version__.__copyright__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mbstrdecoder.__version__.__license__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mbstrdecoder.__version__.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mbstrdecoder.__version__.__maintainer__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {